Just a quick reminder that both lanes of traffic must stop when you see this sign. If the lights are blinking yellow, you need to slow down as the "reds" are about to come on!
We had several vehicles pass a bus on 377 today while stopped and with students outside of the bus; luckily no one was injured and luckily our cameras were able to catch them! Be looking for other flashing "red lights" in the near future!
Let's all keep an eye out for those "big yellow dogs," and let's all help keep our students safe! #TeamWhitesboro

post_text:
COVID - 19 Reminder:

Parents, if anyone in your household is experiencing multiple C-19 symptoms (fever, cough, loss of taste or smell, etc...) please keep them home until you receive a negative test result or an alternative diagnosis. If you are waiting on a test result, everyone in your household must remain in quarantine until those results come back negative. If positive, everyone in your household will then move to a quarantine status for at least 14 days.

Please understand that a quarantine is not punishment. The quarantine is to prevent a "mass" spread of COVID - 19, which would cause a major "shut-down" within the district, not to mention introducing the virus to multiple families. Let's keep each other healthy!

It is also important to note that not everything is COVID - 19. Allergies, Strep throat and various other illnesses are prevalent right now.....and flu season is just around the corner.

Continue to do your daily "self checks" and hopefully, together, we can continue with a safe and healthy school year!

#TeamWhitesboro #WhateverItTakes #bealight

post_text:
Parents of Seniors, given the uncertainty of tomorrow, next week and next month, we have decided to host Senior Night for Band, Cheer, Cross Country, Fall Tennis, The Flag Runners and Football, this Friday at the Whitesboro vs Bells home football game. Football will be recognized during pregame and all others during Halftime!

We know this is a little earlier than normal however we did not want to run into a situation that would cause us to miss it completely, thus, not being able to honor our Seniors that have been dedicated to their craft, and their Bearcats, for so long!

With UIL restricting capacity of all athletic venues, our participants and their families will have first priority when purchasing opens up (most likely Monday at 12:00). We will have more details regarding tickets in the next couple of days.

Look for a complete "Football Protocol" to be posted here on Monday. Enjoy your weekend and Go Bearcats!
#BOROTUFF #TeamWhitesboro #BeALight #WhateverItTakes

J.W. “Dub” Hayes Primary School
August 18 at 7:16 PM ·

HPS student Drop-off and Pick-up Maps.

Please follow these maps in the morning for student drop-off and after school dismissal. Doors will open at 7:20am, with the tardy bell at 7:50. We will have lots of staff outside to assist getting students to the correct classrooms.

Walk ups are discouraged, as it limits our ability to socially distance. As we move forward this will be the expectation for student drop-off and pick-up.

Student safety is our main priority. Please be patient with the students and staff and follow the routes outlined for your child's grade.

PreK will begin dismissal at 3:00 with staggered release times.
Kindergarten will begin dismissal at 3:15.
1st and 2nd will begin dismissal at 3:30

We are looking forward to having students back in the halls!

post_text:
We've never been more excited to see traffic backed up on 4th street! Tomorrow starts our 2020-2021 school year and we are ready to make it a great year!

Please allow time in your commute tomorrow (you may want to go ahead and let the boss know you will be a little late) as there will be a learning curve for all of us. New arrival/screening practices will be in place and there will simply be "new" people arriving at each campus. Be patient, as always, it will work itself out in the days to come.

We at WISD look forward to the adventure ahead and we can't wait to see, teach and love on your kids! Our teachers are ready! Let's make this a great year, together! #TeamWhitesboro #bealight #WhateverItTakes

J.W. “Dub” Hayes Primary School
August 15 at 1:09 PM ·

Attention 2nd and 1st grade parents;

2nd grade school supplies dropoff scheduled for Monday 8/17/20 will be moved to the horseshoe area in the front of Hayes Primary. They are re-paving the parket lot by the tennis courts, and we cannot have traffic in that area on Monday. We apologize for this inconvenience. See you Monday at the following times in the front of HPS for 2nd grade supplies drop off from 8:00-10:00am and 4:00-6:00pm. Please pull forward as far as possible when dropping of supplies.

1st grade supplies drop off is still as scheduled. It is Monday 8/17/20 from 8:00-10:00am and 4:00-6:00pm at the 1st grade drop off area on the west side of the school (football field side). The 1st grade teachers will be under the second awning towards the back of the building.
Thank you, we are very excited to see the kids and get the new school year started!

Hayes Primary School is now taking
>>> appointments only <<<
for Incoming Kindergarten students for 2020-21
through June 15th!

Please call Amy Pirtle at 903-564-4281 or
email: pirtlea@whitesboroisd.org

Items needed to enroll:

+Child’s Birth Certificate
+Child’s Social Security Card
+Immunization Record
+Parent/Guardian Driver’s License OR
State Issued Photo ID
+Proof of Residency (Electric, Water, Gas Bill or Lease)
+Any Legal Paperwork- Ex: Custody, Divorce, Power of Attorney, DFPS Paperwork.

*** Please help us spread the word***

post_text:
At this time, all K-8 students who checked out Chromebooks, library books, and calculators from the district need to return them in order to clear their records for final report card mailout & promotion to the next grade. On Thursday, May 21st, they can be returned from 10am-12noon and 4-6pm at Whitesboro Middle school in the west parking lot. Please be sure to bring the charger with the Chromebook for return.

The high school will be collecting all Chromebooks this Friday to update them. We will make arrangements for those that may need them for summer school. Please be sure to bring the charger with the Chromebook for return. Seniors will get theirs back if paid in full when they pick up their diplomas later in June.
9th grade 2:00
10th grade 3:00
11th grade 4:00
Seniors 5:00 or bring when lining up for parade.
Families may bring at one time. Please bring any other items needing to be returned as well. Library books, textbooks, calculators, etc...
Please bring to the South side of school at student drop off. We will be outside to collect. See you then.

shared_text:
Whitesboro Athletics
April 29 at 12:43 PM ·

Sad day! But one that had to happen! We have cleaned out all our athletic lockers and placed all personal belongings in bags with your students names on them.

We will be collecting any athletic gear your child may have of the schools and returning their personal belongings on Wednesday May 6th from 10 AM to noon.

We will have a pick up line at the MS using the carport next to the gym on west side parking lot (normal parent drop off and pick up point) for all MS athletes.

At the HS we will use the gym roll up door on east side of campus for girls athletics and the north locker room door closest to Hwy 82 for boys athletics.

We ask that you stay in your cars and simply give us our things and we will track down your students bags and bring them to your vehicle.

See you all next week!

post_text:
Distance Learning Opportunities are going out this Thursday and Friday!! Parent pick-up and bus delivery schedule below:

Parent Pick-up:
Thursday, March 26th: 10:00-12:00 and 4:00-6:00, at all campuses (refer to maps below)(Pick a time and swing by) Be Patient, it will be a process but we will move as fast as we can!

Bus Delivery:
Friday, March 27th: Buses will Leave WISD @ 11:00am. Have your students, or a parent, standing at their normal pick-up/drop-off locations. (On a Typical morning, all WISD buses leave town at 6:00am, judge your time based off of this scale.)(example: If my child usually gets picked up at 6:40am, then on Friday the bus should be by around 11:40am.) These trips will take longer than usual as we have to check-out and verify each student as well as give each student a weeks worth of breakfast and lunch!!!

(All packets not picked up on Thursday or delivered on Friday will be mailed home on Friday afternoon)

#TeamWhitesboro #LeaveYourMark #BOROTUFF #Whateverittakes

post_text: WISD Food Service is the BEST!!! Our students are loved on and fed daily by some of the most caring ladies you will find!.......and the food is fantastic! #TeamWhitesboro #LeaveYourMark #Whateverittakes
shared_text:
Alicia Tracy is with Sheila Johnston and 10 others.
February 26 at 1:05 PM ·

Texas Agriculture Commissioner Sid Miller recognized the Whitesboro ISD Cafeterias with the Best of the Bunch Award for reaching top level in the Texas Department of Agriculture Farm Fresh Challenge! Every October, participating schools pledge to incorporate more local products in meals and provide important lessons about healthy lifestyles and Texas Agriculture. The challenge was: Eat Local. Teach Local. Be Social. We are doing our part to support local farmers, ranchers, and distributors by bringing these healthy Texas foods to school meals and teaching children about the value of agriculture.
Whitesboro ISD Cafes served Texas products EVERY DAY in October 2019! We invited a Texas rancher out to speak to the students about raising cattle. We served local fresh fruits and vegetables daily with the Farm to School program.
Just another way school lunches are changing for the better! Come eat with us & eat healthy & local! #TeamWhitesboro #WhateverItTakes #RealSchoolFood #TexasFarmFreshChallenge

Whitesboro High School
February 8 at 3:31 PM ·

Way to go lady wrestlers!! This weekend the Whitesboro Lady Cats competed in the 2020 8 5A District wrestling tournament @ The Colony High School. Junior Kira Phillips placed 3rd with a defeat over Malia Nguyen of Wakeland, Sophomore Gracie McNamara placed 4th and Senior Jocelyn Giron placed 6th. Both Phillips and McNamara will advance to the regional tournament on February 14 at Frisco Independence High School. Top four placers from the regional tournament will advance to the state tournament in Houston on February 21st.

post_text:
We are watching the weather closely and most certainly hold our student's and staff's safety as our highest priority. At this time we are maintaining a regular school day schedule to allow parents time to return home to be with their "bus" riding students.

All campuses have plans in place in case there is severe weather, however, please feel free to pick your child up early if you deem it necessary.

In the event that severe weather occurs at the point of dismissal, our students will shelter in place until the severe weather passes. Buses will then run their regular routes.

Tonight's games at home vs S and S are still scheduled to start at 4:30. The relative closeness of our districts allow for a "game time decision." In the event that severe weather strikes during a basketball game, all students and fans will be asked to relocate to "shelter" areas adjacent to the gyms.

Technically it's not "Spring time in Texas," but then again, it is Texas!

Extra Counselors will be available for the remainder of the semester if your student needs to visit with anyone. The WHS office staff will have "substitutes" filling in for the remainder of the day so please be understanding when calling in.

post_text: Our students and our faculty (some of which may, or may not, be afraid of clowns), really enjoyed the Fire Prevention Week assemblies last week! We are truly blessed in Whitesboro with amazing first responders!!! #TeamWhitesboro #BOROTUFF #Whateverittakes
shared_text:
Whitesboro Fire Department
October 21, 2019 at 3:10 PM ·

In the excitement of the Peanut Festival and weather patterns of last night, we want to be sure we don't overlook the hard work and dedication our fire prevention crew put in to fire prevention this year. They started working on the program months ago and it culminated in a presentation to the WISD students. In the process, our clowns were able to run the tunnel with the football team (thankfully they weren't trampled), help staff face their fear of clowns, visit locals out shopping, and get suspicious looks from bank staff as they announced their arrival at First United (thankfully the panic button was never pushed). A big thank you to Michael Gravette, Brandon Prough, Michael Parish, Bill Sharon and Dillion Kirby for their hard work, as well as several other roadies and assistants who helped the day of the show.

August 12, 2019 at 10:54 AM ·

It's a great day to be a Bearcat! #teamwhitesboro we are praying for you.
Members of the Whitesboro Ministerial Alliance packed Goody Bags on Friday night for all 250 Whitesboro ISD employees to welcome them back to school today.
Join the Whitesboro Ministerial Alliance Sunday evening, August 18th at each school campus. Pastors from each church will lead a time of prayer. Following the prayer time will be an Ice Cream social in Wesley Hall at 7:30.
We hope everyone will join us this Sunday as we continue to welcome our neighborhood back to school.

Field Update:

Dirt work is set to begin this Friday and we are projected to be complete on August 20th!!!

We hope to host "Meet the Bearcat" at Bearcat Stadium on August the 23rd, so you will have the opportunity to "walk the field" and "test out" the surface that our students will enjoy for years to come!!

We will have a bank of lights running most nights to allow for the workers to complete as much work as possible while temperatures are at their lowest.

The track will remain CLOSED for the remainder of summer but the end product will be worth it!

#TeamWhitesboro #LeaveYourMark #BOROTUFF

Whitesboro Athletics
May 23, 2019 at 10:16 AM ·

Important Summer Pride info-

All organized workouts will be held on Monday’s thru Thursday’s beginning June 3rd at the WHS weight room / gyms / fields.

HS girls will start at 7:29 AM in practice gym at WHS.

HS boys will start at 7:29 AM in weight room at WHS.

The HS boys and girls will switch at 8:30 and be released by 9:30

MS boys & Girls will begin at 9:30 AM in the WHS weight room and be released by 10:30.

Any student arriving late to their scheduled start time will not be allowed to participate during the organized portion of the workout, but will be allowed to stay on campus and complete their workouts after facilities become available at 10:30 AM. All WHS Athletic facilities will close at 3:30 pm daily.

50 dollars per athlete is due by June 6th and checks can be made out to WISD athletics and given to any coach.

*Scholarships are available by request. Please contact Coach Fagan or The Coach Gabbert’s for approval.

Thank you!

Tag a Teacher!! This week is set apart as a designated week in which we should all take a minute and think about those teachers that truly made an impact on us. We are truly blessed at WISD with teachers that teach from the heart and teach to make a difference!

post_text:
Early voting began today! As you vote you will notice that Whitesboro ISD is calling for a bond election. This bond will be for 1.75 million for the purpose of renovating Bearcat Stadium. The 1.75 million will be generated without an increase in tax rate. WISD currently operates with a .195 cent Interest and Sinking (debt) tax rate and this will NOT increase. Currently our Maintenance and Operations rate sits at 1.17 and, by law, can not increase. In fact, depending upon the legislative session that is currently ongoing, this number may decrease. (The attached rendering is only to provide an example and does not necessarily reflect the final selection.)
Items that may be addressed:
1. Turf playing/marching surface
2. Dressing areas for home and away
3. Press Box
4. Score Board/Sound System
5. Visitor Concessions/Restroom

Currently our Maintenance and Operations rate sits at 1.17 and, by law, can not increase. In fact, depending upon the legislative session that is currently ongoing, this number may decrease. (The attached rendering is only to provide an example and does not necessarily reflect the final selection.)
Items that may be addressed:
1. Turf playing/marching surface
2. Dressing areas for home and away
3. Press Box

post_text:
Next Monday, the Whitesboro Athletic Booster Club is hosting an informal, come and go, community meet and greet for Whitesboro's new Athletic Director and Head Football Coach, Cody Fagan. This will take place just prior to our regularly scheduled April Board Meeting, at the Hayes Primary Cafeteria, from 5:30-7:00. ***Refreshments provided!***
Also, stick around as we honor many students and faculty members for their efforts inside, and outside, of the classrooms! There will also be a couple of presentations regarding our upcoming Bond Election that is centered around facility updates to Bearcat Stadium.
This should be an exciting evening and we look forward to seeing you there! #TeamWhitesboro

post_text: Thank you West Grayson RSPA for your continued support of these young learners and for grabbing these "Big Bearcats" to come spread the love of reading! #TeamWhitesboro #LeaveYourMark
shared_text:
West Grayson RSPA
February 8, 2019 at 1:36 PM ·

West Grayson RSPA's book project had a great send off today Whitesboro Intermmediate School. Whitesboro High School athletes wrote inspirational sayings on the backs of bookmarks and assisted in distributing books to each third grader. In addition they read the book aloud to the youngsters and peaked their interest in it's exciting content about surviving a bear attack. The young athletes spent time with their listeners emphasizing the importance of reading, cultivating good health and study habits and having goals as incentives. More pictures of the groups reading books will follow for several days.

post_text: This afternoon Whitesboro Middle School Administrators were made aware of threatening comments made by 1 individual. This individual was questioned and removed from Campus pending further investigation. An additional police presence will be at WMS tomorrow to provide a greater sense of security for our students and staff. This presence will also enforce how serious these types of comments are taken regardless of whether they are serious or in jest. As a reminder, speak to your children about "speaking out" anytime they are concerned with the actions, behaviors or comments of a fellow student.

post_text: Way to go WHS Cross Country!! Amazing job by all! #TeamWhitesboro #LeaveYourMark
shared_text:
Whitesboro Athletic Booster Club
November 3, 2018 at 4:54 PM ·

🏃‍♀️ 🏃 Cross County State 🏃‍♀️ 🏃

A memorable state XC meet. Kelli pr'd for the season, Michael is the state runner up and pr'd, and Max medaled in 9th place. And even though the boys team was only 8 points from the medal stand, the fact that they posted the fastest Whitesboro xc team time ever and the best Whitesboro xc team place in state meet is testament that hard work, determination, and working as a team pays off. Osvaldo is the third fastest 9th grade xc runner in Texas 3A. I am looking forward to the future teams. Thanks to all the parents, Brad, and Coach Garner for always being there for these young athletes. As max and Michael received their medals, my eyes got a little misty. I am going to miss the inspiration the seniors, Michael- max- Manuel- Kelli- emma- and Kayla, have been to the other runners. But, I have no doubt next year's team captain's will be ready to step into those shoes.
Coach Urban

shared_text:
Freddie Beckwith is with Bailey Galewaler and 5 others at Whitesboro High School.
September 23, 2018 at 5:11 PM · Whitesboro, TX ·

I thought I'd post a few more images from the WHS homecoming and let you all know you have an awesome football environment in Whitesboro! In spite of the horrendous weather the stadium was rocking! The field was in great shape (it may not be now), the lighting was great (good for me), the crowd was loud, cheerleaders cheering (in the rain), and the band played ALL GAME LONG. It was as if I was shooting a playoff game! You should be very proud and I hope I can shoot there again soon. Thanks for having me!
